tion%20called%20spasmodic%20dysphonia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20began%20as%20a%20mild%20tremble%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oprah.com%2Fomagazine%2Foprah-interviews-robert-kennedy-jr%2Fall%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKennedy%20told%20Oprah%20Winfrey%20in%20a%202007%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20believed%20his%20condition%20worsened%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20we%20know%20about%20the%20disorder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20is%20spasmodic%20dysphonia%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESpasmodic%20dysphonia%20is%20a%20neurological%20disorder%20that%20causes%20involuntary%20spasms%20in%20the%20muscles%20of%20the%20voice%20box%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20larynx%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hopkinsmedicine.org%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-and-diseases%2Fspasmodic-dysphonia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20John%20Hopkins%20Medicine.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20vocal%20cords%20don't%20vibrate%20as%20they%20typically%20should.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20condition%20can%20strain%20an%20individual's%20ability%20to%20speak%2C%20sometimes%20causing%20their%20voice%20to%20sound%20hoarse%20or%20breathy.%20Humming%2C%20laughing%2C%20singing%2C%20swallowing%2C%20and%20crying%20can%20also%20be%20impacted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F7amP7U7A9fM%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20kinds%20of%20spasmodic%20dysphonia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20common%20type%20is%20adductor%20spasmodic%20dysphonia%2C%20in%20which%20the%20vocal%20cords%20tighten%20up%2C%20causing%20a%20person's%20voice%20to%20sound%20strained%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Fdiseases%2F21838-spasmodic-dysphonia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Cleveland%20Clinic%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20medical%20center%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbductor%20spasmodic%20dysphonia%20is%20where%20the%20muscle%20spasms%20cause%20the%20vocal%20folds%20to%20stay%20open.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20a%20person's%20voice%20can%20sound%20breathy%2C%20according%20to%20the%20medical%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20can%20have%20a%20rare%20mix%20of%20both%20types.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20causes%20spasmodic%20dysphonia%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20exact%20cause%20of%20spasmodic%20dysphonia%20is%20unknown%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uofmhealth.org%2Fconditions-treatments%2Fear-nose-throat%2Fspasmodic-dysphonia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Michigan%20Medicine%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSpasmodic%20dysphonia%20is%20thought%20to%20be%20caused%20by%20abnormal%20functioning%20in%20an%20area%20of%20the%20brain%20called%20the%20basal%20ganglia%2C%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nidcd.nih.gov%2Fhealth%2Fspasmodic-dysphonia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Institute%20on%20Deafness%20and%20Other%20Communication%20Disorders%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20basal%20ganglia%20help%20coordinate%20the%20movements%20of%20muscles%20throughout%20the%20body.%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20has%20also%20found%20abnormalities%20in%20the%20areas%20of%20the%20cerebral%20cortex%20%E2%80%94%20the%20area%20of%20the%20brain%20that%20controls%20muscle%20movement%2C%20the%20NIDCD%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpasmodic%20dysphonia%20may%20also%20be%20inherited%2C%20but%20a%20specific%20gene%20for%20the%20disorder%20has%20not%20yet%20been%20identified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIs%20spasmodic%20dysphonia%20painful%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20condition%20is%20not%20known%20to%20be%20painful%2C%20but%20it%20does%20make%20the%20ability%20to%20speak%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20if%20it%20hurts%20to%20talk%2C%20Kennedy%20told%20Winfrey%3A%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20but%20it's%20an%20effort.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKennedy%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DCC66Mh7C2nA%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20told%20NewsNation%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20feels%20the%20condition%20makes%20it%20%26quot%3Bproblematical%26quot%3B%20for%20people%20to%20listen%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20cannot%20listen%20to%20myself%20on%20TV%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20joked.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20feel%20sorry%20for%20you%20guys%20having%20to%20listen%20to%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECan%20spasmodic%20dysphonia%20be%20cured%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESymptoms%20of%20spasmodic%20dysphonia%2C%20which%20is%20a%20chronic%20condition%2C%20often%20develop%20around%20middle%20age%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.asha.org%2Fpublic%2Fspeech%2Fdisorders%2Fspasmodic-dysphonia%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20American%20Speech-Language-Hearing%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20symptoms%20can%20also%20be%20more%20acute%20when%20under%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20cure%20for%20the%20condition%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pennmedicine.org%2Ffor-patients-and-visitors%2Fpatient-information%2Fconditions-treated-a-to-z%2Fspasmodic-dysphonia%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSpasmodic%2520dysphonia%252C%2520also%2520known%2520as%2Ccan%2520be%2520improved%2520through%2520treatment.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%20Health%20System%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20there%20are%20treatment%20options%20available%2C%20including%20speech%20therapy%20and%20psychological%20counseling%20to%20treat%20mild%20cases.%20Botox%20injections%20are%20also%20an%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEach%20Botox%20injection%20provides%20about%20three%20months%20of%20relief%20from%20symptoms%20and%20there%20is%20no%20limit%20to%20the%20number%20of%20Botox%20injections%20you%20may%20receive%20for%20this%20condition%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Penn%20Medicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20rare%20is%20spasmodic%20dysphonia%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20disorder%20is%20rare%20and%20impacts%20about%201%20per%20100%2C000%20people%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4940852%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSpasmodic%2520dysphonia%2520is%2520rare%253B%2520some%2Ca%2520significant%2520roadblock%2520to%2520research.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%202011%20study%20published%20in%20The%20Journal%20of%20Neuroscience%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20notable%20people%20with%20spasmodic%20dysphonia%20include%20%26quot%3BHellboy%26quot%3B%20actress%20Selma%20Blair%2C%20CBS%20News%20correspondent%20Jeff%20Pegues%2C%20and%20journalist%20Diane%20Rehm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKennedy's%20campaign%20team%20could%20not%20provide%20comment%20before%20the%20time%20of%20this%20story's%20publishing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-rfk-jr-voice-raspy-cause-spasmodic-dysphonia-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692317004000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64de9f84b698ac0019dbd7b1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%