se%20in%20China%20this%20month%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20such%20drill%20between%20those%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EWhile%20deepening%20defense%20research%20and%20security%20ties%20between%20Beijing%20and%20the%20Arab%20Gulf%20states%20aren't%20surprising%20to%20the%20US%2C%20they%20remain%20%26quot%3Bconcerning%20for%20US%20national%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20Hawthorne%20said%2C%20but%20that%20likely%20won't%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20threat%20if%20those%20countries%20%26quot%3Bmaintain%20their%20currently%20robust%20security%2C%20intelligence%2C%20and%20political%20relationships%20with%20Washington%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Abu%20Dhabi%20Mohammed%20bin%20Zayed%20China%20Xi%20Jinping%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64de9ae3b698ac0019dbd3af%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAbu%20Dhabi%20Crown%20Prince%20Mohammed%20bin%20Zayed%20with%20Xi%20in%20Beijing%20in%20July%202019.%3Cp%3EANDY%20WONG%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EAboudouh%20said%20the%20US%20had%20%26quot%3Bspecific%20concerns%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20UAE's%20%26quot%3Bintensifying%20military%20relations%26quot%3B%20with%20Beijing%2C%20as%20well%20as%20dismay%20about%20Saudi%20Arabia%20receiving%20Chinese%20help%20with%20its%20civilian%20nuclear%20program%20and%20%26quot%3Bsuspicions%20of%20a%20separate%20ballistic-missile%20program.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EAboudouh%20argued%20that%20if%20the%20US%20is%20worried%20about%20%26quot%3Bincreasing%20military%20exchanges%26quot%3B%20between%20China%20and%20Arab%20Gulf%20states%2C%20it%20should%20%26quot%3Btackle%20the%20rising%20perceptions%20of%20declining%20US%20commitment%20to%20regional%20security.%26quot%3B%20If%20those%20countries%20aren't%20getting%20what%20they%20want%20from%20the%20US%2C