0moved%20when%20it%20was%20already%20a%20skeleton.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20this%20bizarre%20occurrence%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20linked%20at%20least%20to%20superstition%20or%20folklore%20about%20the%20way%20disease%20spread%20through%20dead%20bodies%20at%20the%20time%2C%20if%20not%20vampire%20lore%20exactly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBodies%20were%20sometimes%20exhumed%20and%20burned%3Cp%3EBarber's%20post-mortem%20fate%20may%20have%20coincided%20with%20a%C2%A0%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fhistory%2Fthe-great-new-england-vampire-panic-36482878%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evampire%20panic%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20that%20swept%20the%20region%20in%20the%20late%201800s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20New%20England%20vampire%20scare%20impacted%20a%20family%20in%20Connecticut%20that%20came%20to%20be%20known%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.registercitizen.com%2Fnews%2Farticle%2FIn-1854-vampire-panic-struck-Connecticut-town-12156066.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BJewett%20City%20vampires.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201894%2C%20several%20members%20of%20the%20Ray%20family%20died%20of%20consumption%2C%20now%20known%20as%20tuberculosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Rays%20decided%20they%20needed%20to%20keep%20their%20deceased%20relatives%20from%20coming%20back%20to%20life%20and%20killing%20their%20living%20family%20members%2C%20state%20Archaeologist%20Nicholas%20Bellantoni%20and%20municipal%20historian%20Mary%20Deveau%20said%20in%20a%202008%20tour%20covered%20by%20local%20news%20outlet%20The%20Register%20Citizen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20chose%20to%20exhume%20two%20of%20the%20sons%20who%20had%20died%20from%20the%20disease%20and%20burn%20them%20%26quot%3Bon%20the%20spot%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20newspaper%20reports%20that%20recounted%20the%20event%20eight%20years%20after%20it%20happened%2C%20per%20the%20Register%20Citizen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBricks%20or%20stones%20were%20placed%20in%20their%20mouths%20to%20prevent%20the%20dead%20from%20chewing%20their%20way%20out%20of%20the%20ground%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20skull%20with%20a%20dislocated%20jaw%20and%20a%20stone%20place%20in%20its%20mouth%20is%20shown%20from%20the%20side.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dd3f104ef9f30019f8a3b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EItalian%20researchers%20believe%20they%20found%20the%20remains%20of%20a%20female%20%26quot%3Bvampire%26quot%3B%20from%2016th-century%20Venice%2C%20buried%20with%20a%20brick%20in%20her%20mouth%20to%20prevent%20her%20feasting%20on%20plague%20victims.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FHandout%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBricks%20and%20stones%20weren't%20only%20used%20to%20weigh%20the%20bodies%20down.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20these%20were%20carefully%20placed%20in%20the%20mouth%20of%20the%20deceased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20case%20was%20uncovered%20in%20Italy%20in%202009%2C%20when%20the%20remains%20of%20a%20woman%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-italy-vampire%2Fvampire-unearthed-in-venice-plague-grave-idUSTRE52B4RU20090312%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E16th-century%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20found%20buried%20with%20a%20large%20brick%20jammed%20into%20her%20mouth.%20The%20woman%20was%20found%20in%20a%20mass%20grave%20and%20may%20have%20died%20from%20bubonic%20plague%2C%20which%20was%20spreading%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Borrini%2C%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20dig%2C%20this%20was%20one%20of%20the%20prime%20examples%20of%20a%20burial%20people%20would%20have%20done%20at%20the%20time%20for%20a%20type%20of%20vampire%20from%20European%20folklore%2C%20a%20Nachzehrer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20classical%20idea%20that%20the%20vampire%20is%20going%20out%20and%20sucking%20the%20blood%20of%20people.%20It's%20more%20someone%20that%20is%20killing%20people%20from%20the%20grave%20before%20being%20able%20to%20then%20rise%20as%20a%20full%20vampire%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EStones%20were%20also%20placed%20in%20mouths%20to%20prevent%20the%20soul%20from%20entering%20or%20leaving%20the%20body%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22846%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20skull%20is%20seen%20in%20situ%2C%20a%20rock%20is%20placed%20in%20the%20child's%20mouth.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dd405f4ef9f30019f8a45f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22635%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20body%20of%20a%20child%20found%20in%20a%205th-century%20Italian%20cemetery%20buried%20with%20a%20stone%20in%20their%20mouth.%3Cp%3EDavid%20Pickel%2FStanford%20University%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStones%20had%20also%20been%20used%20in%20unusual%20burial%20practices%20much%20earlier%20than%20that.%20That's%20the%20case%20of%20a%20child%2C%20about%2010%20years%20old%2C%20who%20died%20in%20the%205th%20century%20and%20was%20found%20in%20the%20ruins%20of%20an%20Ancient%20Roman%20villa%2C%20in%20Teverina%2C%20Italy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stone%20may%20have%20been%20a%20way%20to%20keep%20the%20child%2C%C2%A0who%20is%20thought%20to%20have%20died%20of%20malaria%2C%20from%20spreading%20the%20disease%20or%20generally%20tormenting%20the%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20also%20a%20very%20ancient%20idea%20of%20breath%20being%20linked%20to%20life%20and%20the%20soul%20and%20the%20mouth%20in%20particular%20as%20being%20sort%20of%20the%20portal%20through%20which%20the%20soul%20exits%20after%20death%2C%26quot%3B%20Jordan%20Wilson%2C%20a%20bio%20archaeologist%20and%20lead%20on%20the%20dig%2C%20told%20Insider%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20could%20also%20have%20been%20with%20the%20intent%20to%20keep%20the%20child's%20body%20safe%20from%20witches%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EStakes%20were%20placed%20through%20the%20heart%20and%20used%20to%20pin%20bodies%20to%20the%20ground%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20aged%20skeleton%20is%20seen%20with%20a%20large%20block%20of%20iron%20placed%20near%20its%20chest%20under%20the%20armpit.%20Its%20teeth%20are%20missing%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ddf947bd8c0900184edebe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221503%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20skeleton%20pierced%20with%20a%20piece%20of%20iron%20is%20seen%20on%20display%20during%20a%20media%20event%20at%20the%20National%20History%20Museum%20in%20Sofia%20June%2014%2C%202012%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FStoyan%20Nenov%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20also%20common%20practice%20to%20try%20to%20pin%20the%20bodies%20to%20the%20ground%20in%20some%20way%20or%20another%2C%20Borrini%20told%20Insider%20last%20year.%20This%20can%20be%20done%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20by%20fastening%20the%20body's%20shroud%20to%20the%20coffin%20with%20nails%20or%20placing%20symbolic%20rose%20thorns%20on%20their%20graves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20people%20in%20the%20middle%20ages%20in%20Bulgaria%20seem%20to%20have%20taken%20that%20concept%20one%20step%20further.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20archaeologists%20uncovered%20two%20bodies%20that%20were%20buried%20with%20iron%20stakes%20through%20their%20hearts%2C%20intended%20to%20pin%20them%20down%20and%20prevent%20a%20return%20from%20the%20dead.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20skeletons%20stabbed%20with%20rods%20illustrate%20a%20practice%20which%20was%20common%20in%20some%20Bulgarian%20villages%20up%20until%20the%20first%20decade%20of%20the%2020th%20Century%2C%26quot%3B%20Bozhidar%20Dimitrov%2C%20who%20was%20head%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.historymuseum.org%2F%3Flang_id%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20History%20Museum%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Bulgarian%20capital%20Sofia%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20discovery%2C%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-18334106%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBBC%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fways-villagers-buried-vampires-to-stop-rising-from-dead-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692308454000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dd557e4ef9f30019f8afdd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fways-villagers-buried-vampires-to-stop-rising-from-dead-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22People%20associated%20%26quot%3Bvampiric%26quot%3B%20outbreaks%20with%20mass%20deaths%20that%20were%20unexplainable%20at%20the%20time%2C%20but%20are%20now%20assumed%20to%20have%20been%20caused%20by%20disease.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis%2CErin%20Snodgrass%2CMarianne%20Guenot)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fways-villagers-buried-vampires-to-stop-rising-from-dead-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98My%20Mother%2C%20the%20Monster%2C%E2%80%99%20About%20a%20Mom%20Who%20Dons%20a%20Scary%20Mask%2C%20Wins%20CineLink%20Award%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692308381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FMy-Mother-the-Monster.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235699232%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Oliv%C3%A9r%20Rudolf%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9CMy%20Mother%2C%20the%20Monster%E2%80%9D%20has%20won%20the%20Eurimages%20C