.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20advice%20I%20received%20from%20my%20high%20school's%20college%20counselor%20(along%20with%20most%20of%20my%20teachers)%20when%20I%20shared%20my%20intention%20to%20apply%20to%20Yale%20University.%20As%20an%20Asian%20American%20student%20with%20a%203.7%20unweighted%20GPA%2C%20he%20said%2C%20I%20had%20no%20chance%20of%20getting%20into%20such%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fpreferred-cheap-community-college-over-georgetown-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprestigious%20university%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0Typically%20most%20Asian%20Americans'%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.highereddive.com%2Fnews%2Fasian-american-students-admissions-disadvantage-white-students%2F690152%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrades%20skew%20higher%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20they%20need%20a%20perfect%20GPA%20to%20get%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20this%20and%20similar%20interactions%2C%20I%20was%20made%20keenly%20aware%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F12%2F02%2Fus%2Fasian-american-college-applications.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epervasive%20prejudice%20against%20Asian%20Americans%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20college-admissions%20process%20at%20elite%20universities.%20For%20many%2C%20anti-Asian%20bias%20in%20college%20admissions%20was%20an%20open%20secret%20or%20a%20widely%20spread%20rumor.%20But%20for%20myself%20and%20fellow%20Asian%20American%20applicants%2C%20it%20was%20an%20ever-present%20obstacle%20to%20overcome.%20At%20every%20turn%2C%20I%20was%20reminded%20that%20I%20was%20competing%20against%20other%2C%20more-qualified%20Asian%20American%20students%20and%20that%20I%20was%20fighting%20to%20defy%20rampant%20stereotypes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgainst%20the%20odds%2C%20I%20was%20the%20only%20student%20from%20my%20high%20school%20to%20receive%20a%20coveted%20acceptance%20letter%20from%20Yale.%C2%A0I%20now%20help%20other%20Asian%20Americans%20get%20into%20their%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fa-day-in-the-life-senior-georgetown-university-college-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edream%20schools%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20worked%20hard%20to%20get%20into%20Yale%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20opened%20my%20acceptance%20letter%20in%202013%2C%20I%20was%20shocked.%20Everyone%20around%20me%20told%20me%20that%20this%20was%20a%20nearly%20impossible%20accomplishment%20as%20an%20Asian%20American%20student%2C%20especially%20one%20with%20my%20grades.%20The%20acceptance%20rate%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foir.yale.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fw033_fresh_admissions.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyear%20at%20Yale%20was%20just%206.9%25%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20couldn't%20believe%20that%20I%20had%20defied%20the%20statistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20later%20discover%20through%20a%20conversation%20with%20the%20admissions%20officer%20who%20read%20my%20application%20that%20it%20was%20my%20passion%20%E2%80%94%20demonstrated%20through%20my%20activities%20outside%20the%20classroom%20%E2%80%94%20that%20had%20earned%20me%20a%20spot%20at%20one%20of%20the%20US's%20top%20universities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20teenager%2C%20I%20experienced%20the%20pain%20of%20losing%20a%20family%20friend%20to%20suicide.%20The%20ordeal%20sparked%20a%20passion%20in%20me%20for%20instructing%20others%20about%20bystander%20intervention%20and%20facilitating%20emotionally%20intelligent%20education%20in%20the%20classroom.%20A%20fellow%20student%20and%20I%20poured%20all%20of%20our%20time%20and%20energy%20into%20developing%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20brought%20education%20in%20bystander%20intervention%20and%20mental-health%20awareness%20to%20middle%20schools%20in%20our%20area.%20My%20grades%20suffered%20as%20I%20prioritized%20sending%20cold%20emails%20and%20letters%20soliciting%20businesses%20for%20donations%20and%20sponsorships%20rather%20than%20studying%20for%20biology%20exams%20or%20editing%20essays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20its%20effect%20on%20my%20GPA%2C%20I%20learned%20it%20was%20this%20initiative%20that%20differentiated%20me%20from%20thousands%20of%20other%20applicants.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThat%20same%20passion%20has%20continued%20to%20inform%20me%20as%20a%20college-admissions%20consultant%20for%20students%20with%20diverse%20racial%20and%20socioeconomic%20backgrounds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202015%2C%20I%20have%20worked%20with%20hundreds%20of%20other%20young%20students%20with%20Ivy%20League%20dreams%20%E2%80%94%20one-third%20of%20whom%20are%20Asian%20American.%20My%20approach%20to%20college-admissions%20consulting%20draws%20from%20my%20experience%20leveraging%20my%20passion%20to%20enact%20positive%20change%20in%20my%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20help%20applicants%20discover%20their%20authentic%20passions%20and%20articulate%20them%20to%20admissions%20committees%20at%20top%20universities.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20I%20have%20seen%20students%20develop%20meaningful%20projects%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it's%20starting%20businesses%2C%20founding%20nonprofits%2C%20or%20conducting%20cutting-edge%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20witnessed%20the%20role%20of%20students'%20passions%20in%20giving%20dimension%20and%20dynamism%20to%20their%20applications.%20Clearly%20and%20compellingly%20conveying%20their%20interests%20and%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20they%20have%20mobilized%20those%20interests%20in%20service%20of%20their%20communities%20transforms%20applicants%20from%20numbers%20on%20a%20page%20to%20whole%20people%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20admissions%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDespite%20my%20best%20intentions%2C%20I%20have%20found%20myself%20in%20the%20unenviable%20position%20my%20guidance%20counselor%20found%20himself%20in%2010%20years%20ago%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWell%20aware%20of%20the%20prevalence%20of%20anti-Asian%20bias%20in%20the%20college-admissions%20process%2C%20I%20have%20advised%20students%20to%20pursue%20certain%20activities%20over%20others%20that%20may%20pigeonhole%20them%20in%20stereotypes%20and%20caricatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20told%20an%20award-winning%20pianist%20that%20she%20would%20have%20better%20odds%20of%20admission%20if%20she%20wrote%20about%20her%20interest%20in%20creative%20writing%20instead%20of%20the%20piano%20in%20her%20application%20essay%20because%20the%20topic%20would%20lend%20itself%20to%20stereotypes.%20I%20advised%20yet%20another%20applicant%20early%20in%20their%20high-school%20career%20to%20pursue%20their%20interest%20in%20psychology%2C%20rather%20than%20math%2C%20for%20the%20same%20reason.%20Both%20students%20earned%20acceptance%20at%20prestigious%20universities%20%E2%80%94%20the%20former%20at%20Stanford%20and%20the%20latter%20at%20Dartmouth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20I%20have%20coached%20students%20to%20discover%20their%20authentic%20interests%2C%20I%20have%20been%20keenly%20aware%20that%20admission%20at%20elite%20colleges%20is%20often%20contingent%20on%20strategy%20rather%20than%20merit.%C2%A0Though%20I%20may%20not%20relish%20telling%20students%20to%20pursue%20other%20interests%20to%20break%20out%20of%20stereotypes%2C%20my%20job%20is%20to%20help%20students%20showcase%20their%20strengths%20and%20demonstrate%20the%20value%20they%20will%20add%20to%20a%20campus%20community%20%E2%80%94%20regardless%20of%20their%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElite-college%20admissions%20have%20%3Cem%3Enever%3C%2Fem%3E%20been%20fair%3B%20I%20coach%20students%20to%20become%20better%20players%20within%20a%20game%20that's%20often%20rigged%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20experience%20proves%20that%20while%20grades%20may%20be%20the%20foundation%20of%20a%20competitive%20application%2C%20they%20aren't%20the%20sum%20total%20of%20what%20prestigious%20colleges%20are%20looking%20for.%20Demonstrated%20passion%20speaks%20louder%20than%20numbers%20on%20a%20page.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20unfairness%20of%20the%20admissions%20system%2C%20I%20fought%20to%20earn%20a%20seat%20at%20Yale.%20Now%20I%20seek%20to%20replicate%20my%20success%20story%20for%20every%20student%20I%20work%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fasian-american-man-accepted-yale-university-college-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692300304000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dd495e4ef9f30019f8a990%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fasian-american-man-accepted-yale-university-college-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20writer%20thought%20he%20didn't%20have%20high%20enough%20grades%20as%20an%20Asian%20American%20to%20get%20into%20Yale.%20He%20got%20in%20anyway.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Christopher%20Rim)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fasian-american-man-accepted-yale-university-college-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Yasin%20Malik's%20wife%20is%20special%20adviser%20to%20Pakistan%20caretaker%20PM%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692300187000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102812635%2Cimgsize-799649.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fyasin-malik-wife-is-special-adviser-to-pakistan-caretaker-pm-as-interim-cabinet-announced%2Farticleshow%2F102812405.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mushaal%20Hussein%20Mullick%20is%20to%20advise%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20caretaker%20PM%20on%20human%20rights%20and%20women%E2%80%99s%20empowerment.%20Yasin%20Malik%20wa